{"word":"ἄσκοπος","slug":"ἄσκοπος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄσκοπος1</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:σκοπέω'><el>σκοπέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>inconsiderate, heedless</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>: <i>unregardful of</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>unseen, invisible</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>not to be seen, unintelligible, obscure</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>: <i>inconceivable, incalculable</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div> <hr/> <el><b>ἄσκοπος2</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:σκοπός'><el>σκοπός</el></a>\n<p/><i>aimless, random</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/>"}]}